'''Aimar Hazar Anwar Sher''' (born 20 December 2002) is an Iraqi professional [[Association football|football]]er who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

==Early life==
Sher was born in Iraq, to ethnic Assyrian/Chaldean parents but moved to Sweden at age four together with his family.<ref name="interview">{{cite web|title=Aimar Sher om debuten|url=https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/landslag/p02/arkiv/landslag/2018/04/aimar-sher-om-debuten/|publisher=Swedish Football Association|date=20 April 2018|accessdate=14 February 2020|language=Swedish}}</ref>

He grew up in [[Stockholm]] and started to play football as a youngster with local clubs [[Mälarhöjdens IK]] and [[Enskede IK]], before joining the academy of [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]] in 2013.<ref name="interview2">{{cite web|title=Aimar Sher summerar trenationsturneringen|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2019/10/p02-aimar-sher/|publisher=Swedish Football Association|date=18 October 2019|accessdate=14 February 2020|language=Swedish}}</ref> Sher was part of the Hammarby side that won the U17 Swedish championship in 2019.<ref name="contract">{{cite web|title=Hammarby tecknar avtal med tre akademispelare|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/hammarby-tecknar-avtal-med-tre-akademispelare/|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=20 November 2019|accessdate=14 February 2020|language=Swedish|archive-date=29 November 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211129202506/https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/hammarby-tecknar-avtal-med-tre-akademispelare/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Hammarby IF===
On 21 August 2019, Sher made his competitive debut for Hammarby in a 3–1 away win against [[IFK Luleå]] in [[Svenska Cupen]].<ref name="cupdebut">{{cite web|title=Komfortabelt cupavancemang på Skogsvallen|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/komfortabelt-cupavancemang-pa-skogsvallen/|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=21 August 2019|accessdate=14 February 2020|language=Swedish|archive-date=13 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013223947/https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/komfortabelt-cupavancemang-pa-skogsvallen/|url-status=dead}}</ref> The next month, on 25 September, Sher made his league debut for the club, coming on as a late substitute in a 3–1 away win against [[IK Sirius Fotboll|IK Sirius]] in [[Allsvenskan]]. He became Hammarby's youngest Allsvenskan debutant so far at age 16 and nine months, surpassing the former record holder [[Isac Lidberg]].<ref name="leaguedebut">{{cite web|title=Dag på jobbet-seger i Uppsala|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/matcher-lagen/herr/matcher/sirius-hammarby-5/|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=25 September 2019|accessdate=14 February 2020|language=Swedish}}</ref> Sher signed his first professional contract with Hammarby on 20 November 2019.<ref name="contract"/>

On 5 August 2020, Sher signed a new two-year contract with Hammarby after establishing himself in the first-team squad.<ref name="extension">{{cite web|title=Hammarby förlänger med Aimar Sher|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/hammarby-forlanger-med-aimar-sher/|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=5 August 2020|accessdate=17 August 2020|language=Swedish|archive-date=18 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210518070702/https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/hammarby-forlanger-med-aimar-sher/|url-status=dead}}</ref> He scored his first competitive goal for the club on 1 November the same year, a stoppage-time equaliser in a 1–1 home draw against [[BK Häcken]].<ref name="firstgoal">{{cite web |title=Räddad poäng i 91:a mot Häcken|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/raddad-poang-i-91a-mot-hacken/|publisher=Hammarby Fotboll|date=1 November 2020|accessdate=2 November 2020|language=Swedish}}</ref> In his full debut season, Sher played 21 games, although the side disappointedly finished 8th in the table.<ref name="profile">{{cite web|title=Aimar Sher|url=https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/cuper-och-serier/information/?scr=player&fplid=dce3ecbe-60b9-4b85-b017-8f3fde347d7f|publisher=Swedish Football Association|language=Swedish|accessdate=14 February 2020}}</ref>

On 30 May 2021, Sher won the [[2020–21 Svenska Cupen]] with Hammarby, through a 5–4 win on penalties (0–0 after full-time) against [[BK Häcken]] in the final, where he scored his attempt.<ref name="cupwin">{{cite web|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/cuper/2021/05/hammarby-cupvinnare-efter-straffdrama/|title=Hammarby cupvinnare efter straffdrama|publisher=[[Swedish Football Association]]|date=30 May 2021|access-date=30 May 2021|language=sv}}</ref><ref name="cupwin2">{{cite web|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/historisk-och-dramatisk-cupfinalseger-mot-hacken/|title=Historisk och dramatisk cupfinalseger mot Häcken|publisher=[[Hammarby Fotboll]]|date=30 May 2021|access-date=30 May 2021|language=sv|archive-date=16 June 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210616235344/https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/historisk-och-dramatisk-cupfinalseger-mot-hacken/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Spezia===
On 19 August 2021, Sher transferred to [[Spezia Calcio|Spezia]] in the [[Serie A]], for a reported fee of around €1,5 million, signing a five-year contract.<ref name="spezia1">{{cite web|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/aimar-sher-klar-for-spezia/|title=Aimar Sher klar för Spezia|publisher=[[Hammarby Fotboll]]|date=19 August 2021|access-date=23 August 2021|language=sv|archive-date=30 October 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211030002715/https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/aimar-sher-klar-for-spezia/|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="spezia2">{{cite web|url=https://www.acspezia.com/it/news/ufficiale-aimar-sher-un-nuovo-calciatore-dello-spezia.22730.html|title=Aimar Sher è un nuovo calciatore dello Spezia|publisher=[[Spezia Calcio]]|date=19 August 2021|access-date=23 August 2021|language=it}}</ref><ref name="spezia3">{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/allsvenskan/sher-saljs-lamnar--bajen-efter-atta-ar/|title=Sher säljs – lämnar Bajen efter åtta år|publisher=[[Expressen]]|date=19 August 2021|access-date=23 August 2021|language=sv}}</ref> On 3 October, he made his competitive debut for the club in a 0–4 home loss against [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acspezia.com/it/match-centre/serie-a-tim-2122-hellas-verona-spezia-4-0.6530.html|title=Serie A TIM 21/22: Hellas Verona-Spezia 4-0|publisher=[[Spezia Calcio]]|date=3 October 2021|access-date=15 December 2021|language=sv}}</ref>

====Loan to Groningen====
On 17 January 2023, Sher was loaned by [[FC Groningen]] in the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Groningen|url=https://www.fcgroningen.nl/nieuws/fc-groningen-voegt-talent-sher-toe-aan-eerste-selectie/|title=FC GRONINGEN VOEGT TALENT SHER TOE AAN EERSTE SELECTIE.|date=17 January 2023|access-date=17 January 2023|language=nl}}</ref>

====Release by Spezia====
On 1 September 2023, his contract with Spezia was terminated by mutual consent.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Spezia|url=https://www.speziacalcio.com/it/news/rescissione-contrattuale-per-jacopo-sala-aimar-sher-e-aurelien-nguiamba.25174.html|title=RESCISSIONE CONTRATTUALE PER JACOPO SALA, AIMAR SHER E AURELIEN NGUIAMBA|trans-title=CONTRACT TERMINATION FOR JACOPO SALA, AIMAR SHER AND AURELIEN NGUIAMBA|date=1 September 2023|access-date=1 September 2023|language=it}}</ref>

==International career==
Sher scored in his debut for the [[Sweden men's national under-17 football team|Swedish U17 national team]] in a 1–2 friendly loss against [[Denmark national under-17 football team|Denmark]] on 18 April 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Knapp förlust mot Danmark|url=https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/landslag/p02/arkiv/landslag/2018/04/knapp-forlust-mot-danmark/|publisher=[[Swedish Football Association]]|date=18 April 2018|accessdate=14 February 2020|language=Swedish}}</ref>

On 7 September 2021, Sher made his debut for the [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Swedish U21 national team]], coming on as a substitute in a 1–1 away draw against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-21 football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]], in the qualification to the [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification|2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Aimar Sher om sin U21-landslagsdebut|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2021/09/u21-aimar-sher-debut/|publisher=[[Swedish Football Association]]|date=8 September 2021|accessdate=21 September 2021|language=Swedish}}</ref>

On 24 February 2025, Sher's request to switch allegiance to [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform}}</ref>

==Personal life==
His first name is an homage to the Argentinian former football player [[Pablo Aimar]].<ref name="interview"/>

